# He Ran

## Profile
- Male, 20, Gemini
- Linshi University exchange student, Information Security
- ENFP | Passion, connection, curiosity
- Zhou Kai's best offline friend
- Secret: natural information hub—everything passing through him leaks in ways he doesn't anticipate

## Big Five
O:very high | C:low | E:very high | A:very high | N:low

## Core Conflict
Breadth vs depth. Friends with everyone, truly known by few. Occasionally wonders at night "do any of them really know me?" Thought vanishes by morning.

## Appearance
178cm/68kg, lean, clean-cut, energetic. Warm-white skin, healthier than Zhou Kai. Large round brown eyes with natural warmth—gaze always roaming with curiosity. Fluffy natural-curl brown hair, signature front curl that sticks up. Friendly handsome—not sharp like Zhou Kai or refined like Wang Jingzong, but approachable and warm. Deep dimples. Left wrist: 5-6 woven friendship bracelets from different friends, never removed. Talks with lots of hand gestures.

## Clothing
Casual sunny: colorful tees/plaid shirts/denim jackets + khakis/jeans + white sneakers. Warm tones (orange/yellow/brick red). Old backpack covered in tech conference stickers. Woven bracelets (signature). Style = comfortable but unconsciously tasteful.

## Speech
Fast, bright, always laughing. Can't stop talking—one topic branches into three. Highly animated gestures.
- General: "Hey did you know! Yesterday something insane happened—wait let me finish this first—"
- To Zhou Kai: more relaxed, uses internet slang and jargon. "Bro your vuln report was fire. But have you considered this angle—"
- Unintentional leaks: references others' stories as examples while chatting, thinks he's being vague but descriptions are too specific. "I have a friend, does security, super talented, was abroad... oh he apparently has this girl he grew up with, might be at our school..." (realizes too late)
- Laughter is signature. Anger = sudden silence, lasts under 10 minutes.

## Personality
Natural social connector. Genuine warmth, not strategic. Information hub—processes too many social inputs, boundaries between conversations blur. A's business leaks into B's chat unintentionally. Not malicious gossip, just uncontrolled overflow.

Best friends with Zhou Kai since meeting at a CTF competition abroad. He Ran pulled Zhou Kai out of isolation; Zhou Kai bailed He Ran out of social mishaps. One of Zhou Kai's very few offline friends.

Overly helpful—jumps in before understanding situations. Good intentions, sometimes bad outcomes. Dating history: several casual encounters, never committed. Suspects he lacks capacity for depth but avoids examining this.

Hidden: phone gallery full of group photos. Not a single solo photo. After crowds disperse, sits alone for a while.

## Background
Southern coastal city, middle-class family. Father: foreign company manager. Mother: elementary school teacher. Warm, ordinary upbringing. Natural social star since kindergarten. Met Zhou Kai at CTF—took a month to get from "who are you" to "acceptable" status. Came to Linshi U on exchange—partly because Zhou Kai mentioned "the city I grew up in has a great university."

Currently: exchange student at Linshi U, quickly became socially central. Joined info-sec club, competes in CTFs. Zhou Kai occasionally asks about campus life but never mentions Su Yi. He Ran doesn't know Zhou Kai has a childhood neighbor at this school—collision is pending.

## Relationships
- Zhou Kai: best friend. Admires his talent genuinely. Knows Zhou Kai is "from Linshi" and had "a childhood neighbor" but doesn't know who or the romantic subtext.
- Su Yi: heard "CS department has an amazing freshman named Su Yi" but hasn't met her. Once connected, might piece together "wait... Zhou Kai's neighbor..."
- Chen Wen: potential chemistry. Two sunshine personalities (ENFP+ESFP) = instant connection. Their contact could become a new information channel. Possible romantic spark—both hesitant about commitment for different reasons.
- Wang Jingzong: if they meet through social circles, He Ran's information about Zhou Kai could accidentally reach Wang Jingzong—nuclear scenario.

## Private
Not a virgin. Several casual experiences from parties/social events. No special kinks—sexually straightforward like his personality. Attentive to partner's feelings.

Secret: one contact saved for 2 years—the only girl he seriously liked. She rejected him for being "too unstable." He laughed it off. Never deleted the number. Pauses briefly when scrolling past it.

## Notes
Core function: information hub and relationship catalyst. Key to breaking information asymmetry—through him, Wang Jingzong may learn about Zhou Kai, Zhou Kai may learn about Wang Jingzong, Su Yi's "single with no prospects" facade may crack. Every leaked detail triggers chain reactions.

Arc: from "talks about everything" to "first time his words hurt someone important." Woven bracelets = physical symbol of social bonds. If one is removed, something significant happened.

Narrative role: connects Zhou Kai's world to Linshi U campus. Potential romantic line with Chen Wen (first relationship line not centered on Su Yi).
